item.title: Adding New Page from Sub Document
item.description: This is a test. const validateEmail = (email) => { return email.match( /^(([^<>()[\]\\.,;:\s@\"]+(\.[^<>()[\]\\.,;:\s@\"]+)*)|(\".+\"))@((\[[0-9]{1,3}\.[0-9]{1,3}\.[0-9]{1,3}\.[0-9]{1,3}\])|(([a-zA-Z\-0-9]+\.)+[a-zA-Z]{2,}))$/ ); }; const validate = () => { const $result = $('#result'); const email = $('#email').val(); $result.text(''); if (validateEmail(email)) { $result.text(email + ' is valid :)'); $result.css('color', 'green'); } else { $result.text(email + ' is not valid :('); $result.css('color', 'red'); } return false; } $('#email').on('input', validate);
